<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>KiteAI X Agent — A1 / A2 Classification Logic</title>
<style>
body{font-family:Calibri,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;color:#1a1a1a;margin:2cm 2.5cm;line-height:1.6}
h1{font-size:22pt;color:#1a56a0;border-bottom:4px solid #1a56a0;padding-bottom:8pt;margin-top:0}
h2{font-size:15pt;color:#1a56a0;border-left:6px solid #1a56a0;padding-left:10pt;margin-top:24pt}
h3{font-size:12pt;color:#0d7a5e;margin-top:16pt;border-bottom:1px solid #cde}
h4{font-size:11pt;color:#7b3fa0;margin-top:12pt}
p{margin:5pt 0}
pre{background:#0d1117;color:#e6edf3;padding:12pt 14pt;border-radius:4pt;font-family:'Courier New',monospace;font-size:10pt;line-height:1.8;white-space:pre-wrap;margin:10pt 0;border-left:4px solid #1a56a0}
code{background:#f0f0f0;padding:1pt 5pt;border-radius:3pt;font-family:'Courier New',monospace;font-size:10pt;color:#1a56a0}
table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:10pt 0;font-size:10pt}
th{background:#1a56a0;color:#fff;padding:6pt 10pt;text-align:left}
td{padding:5pt 10pt;border:1px solid #ccc;vertical-align:top}
tr:nth-child(even) td{background:#f0f5ff}
.box{border:1px solid #b0c8f8;border-left:5px solid #1a56a0;background:#f0f5ff;padding:10pt 14pt;margin:10pt 0}
.box-g{border-left-color:#0d7a5e;background:#f0faf5;border-color:#90d0a0}
.box-y{border-left-color:#b8860b;background:#fffbee;border-color:#e0c060}
.box-r{border-left-color:#c0392b;background:#fff5f5;border-color:#f0a0a0}
.box-p{border-left-color:#7b3fa0;background:#f8f0ff;border-color:#d0a0f0}
ul{margin:5pt 0;padding-left:20pt}li{margin:3pt 0}
hr{border:none;border-top:2px solid #1a56a0;margin:20pt 0}
.tag{display:inline-block;padding:2pt 8pt;border-radius:3pt;font-size:9pt;font-weight:bold}
.tag-g{background:#d1fae5;color:#065f46}
.tag-y{background:#fef3c7;color:#92400e}
.tag-b{background:#dbeafe;color:#1e40af}
.tag-r{background:#fee2e2;color:#991b1b}
.eg{background:#f7f7f7;border:1px dashed #bbb;padding:8pt 12pt;margin:6pt 0;font-style:italic;color:#333}
</style></head><body>

<h1>KiteAI X Agent — Account Classification Logic</h1>
<p style="color:#555;font-size:10pt">
How every discovered account is sorted into the paid-collaboration pipeline &nbsp;|&nbsp;
Buckets: 💰 A1 Confirmed &nbsp;·&nbsp; ✦ A2 Genuine &nbsp;·&nbsp; ⚠ Salesy / Low &nbsp;·&nbsp; ◷ A2 Unscored &nbsp;|&nbsp;
AI: Gemini 2.5 Flash &nbsp;|&nbsp; Authenticity threshold: 60
</p>

<div class="box">
<b>The one question behind everything:</b> <i>"Is this account a creator we could PAY to promote KiteAI to their audience?"</i>
Every account is filtered, scored, and then placed into exactly one bucket based on the answer.
</div>

<h2>1. The Big Picture — How an account reaches a bucket</h2>
<p>An account passes through four checks. It must survive each one to be placed in A1/A2.</p>
<pre>STEP 1  DISCOVERY      Found via keyword search (appears as a tweet author)
STEP 2  HARD FILTER    Dropped if: &lt;100 followers · no tweets · no name · score &lt; 10
STEP 3  TRACK SPLIT    Track A = person/creator (collab)   |   Track B = PR/Brand page (ads only)
STEP 4  PAID CHECK     Bio signals + recent-tweet evidence (regex + Gemini)
                       → explicit | inferred | none | unknown
STEP 5  AUTHENTICITY   For promoters only: score 0-100 (how genuine the promo content reads)
                       → splits A2 into Genuine / Salesy / Unscored</pre>

<div class="box-y">
<b>Key rule:</b> the four visible buckets (A1, A2 Genuine, Salesy, A2 Unscored) only ever contain
<b>Track A accounts that are promoters</b>. Everything else is excluded (covered in Section 3).
</div>

<h2>2. The Four Buckets — logic + condition + example</h2>

<h3>💰 A1 — Confirmed <span class="tag tag-g">explicit</span></h3>
<p><b>Meaning:</b> The account <b>openly states or proves</b> it does paid work — there is no doubt.</p>
<p><b>Logic / condition:</b></p>
<pre>track = 'A'  AND  promotion_type = 'explicit'</pre>
<p><b>How it qualifies (any one):</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Bio openly offers paid work: <code>"DM for collabs"</code>, <code>"media kit"</code>, <code>"rate card"</code>, <code>"open to brand deals"</code>, <code>"collab@email"</code>, <code>"UGC creator"</code></li>
<li>A recent post carries a real <b>disclosure tag</b>: <code>#ad</code>, <code>#sponsored</code>, <code>"paid partnership"</code>, <code>"sponsored by"</code></li>
<li>A post uses a <b>discount code</b> or <b>affiliate link</b> for someone else's product (<code>"use code SAVE20"</code>, <code>?ref=…</code>)</li>
</ul>
<div class="eg">
Example — <b>@creator_jane</b>: bio says "AI content creator · DM for collabs · media kit ↓".
Recent post: "Loving @toolX — use code JANE20 for 20% off #ad". → <b>A1 Confirmed.</b>
</div>

<h3>✦ A2 — Genuine <span class="tag tag-y">inferred</span> + <span class="tag tag-b">authenticity ≥ 60</span></h3>
<p><b>Meaning:</b> <b>Behaves</b> like a paid promoter (no open disclosure), <b>and</b> their promo posts read as
trustworthy, real, first-person experience — the creators we most want to contact.</p>
<p><b>Logic / condition:</b></p>
<pre>track = 'A'  AND  promotion_type = 'inferred'  AND  authenticity_score &gt;= 60</pre>
<p><b>How it qualifies for "inferred" (A2):</b> no <code>#ad</code> tag, but a clear PATTERN — promotes
<b>2+ different brands</b> with calls-to-action/links, OR repeated review+link posts, OR brand giveaways.
<b>Every verdict must quote the exact post that proves it.</b></p>
<p><b>What pushes authenticity ≥ 60 (genuine):</b> first-person ("I've been using…", "switched to…"),
specific details (numbers, timeframes, %), honest/balanced (admits a downside), natural human voice.</p>
<div class="eg">
Example — <b>@devmaxwell</b>: "Been testing @appA and @appB this month — @appA's latency dropped ~40% after
I switched, though @appB's docs are weak 👇 (links)". → 2 brands + CTA + no #ad = inferred;
first-person + real number + admits a downside = authenticity ≈ 75. → <b>A2 Genuine.</b>
</div>

<h3>⚠ Salesy / Low <span class="tag tag-y">inferred</span> + <span class="tag tag-r">authenticity &lt; 60</span></h3>
<p><b>Meaning:</b> Still a likely paid promoter (A2), but the content reads as <b>hype, templated, or ad-like</b> —
kept in a separate bucket so the genuine list stays clean.</p>
<p><b>Logic / condition:</b></p>
<pre>track = 'A'  AND  promotion_type = 'inferred'  AND  authenticity_score &lt; 60</pre>
<p><b>What pulls authenticity below 60 (salesy):</b> pure hype ("GAME-CHANGER", "BEST EVER 🚀🔥"),
spammy CTAs ("buy now", "link in bio", "limited time"), ALL-CAPS bursts, emoji overload, robotic/interchangeable praise.</p>
<div class="eg">
Example — <b>@promo_deals_x</b>: "@appA is an ABSOLUTE GAME-CHANGER 🚀🔥 BEST tool EVER — buy now, link in bio!!".
→ promo behaviour = inferred, but hype-only / pure CTA = authenticity ≈ 25. → <b>Salesy / Low.</b>
</div>

<h3>◷ A2 — Unscored <span class="tag tag-y">inferred</span> + <span class="tag tag-b">no authenticity yet</span></h3>
<p><b>Meaning:</b> Identified as A2, but the authenticity scoring hasn't run yet (e.g. classified from bio
during a run that didn't reach the tweet-authenticity pass, or added before the feature existed).</p>
<p><b>Logic / condition:</b></p>
<pre>track = 'A'  AND  promotion_type = 'inferred'  AND  authenticity_score IS NULL</pre>
<p><b>What happens next:</b> the <b>Resolve Unknowns</b> pass fetches their tweets, scores authenticity,
and moves them into <b>Genuine</b> or <b>Salesy</b>. Unscored is a temporary holding state, not a final verdict.</p>
<div class="eg">
Example — <b>@lifestyle_sam</b>: bio "lifestyle creator · links in bio" → tagged inferred from bio,
but tweets not yet analysed. → <b>A2 Unscored</b> until the next resolve pass scores it.
</div>

<h2>3. Accounts NOT included in these four buckets</h2>
<p>The four buckets are <b>only Track-A promoters</b>. These categories are deliberately excluded — with reasons and examples.</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Excluded group</th><th>Condition</th><th>Why excluded</th><th>Example</th></tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Other / unbadged</b> (Track A, not a promoter)</td>
<td><code>track='A' AND promotion_type IN ('none','unknown')</code></td>
<td>In the collab track but no evidence of paid promotion — not a paid creator</td>
<td>A dev who only tweets tutorials</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Track B — PR / Brand pages</b></td>
<td><code>track='B'</code> (type = PR Page / Brand Page)</td>
<td>Company/news/brand accounts — used for <b>ads-audience targeting</b>, not paid-creator outreach</td>
<td>@SomeAINews, @BrandHQ</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Own-product founders</b></td>
<td>verdict → <code>none</code></td>
<td>Promotes only THEIR OWN product — not hireable to promote KiteAI</td>
<td>"We just shipped v2 of OUR app 🚀"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Researchers / academics / journalists</b></td>
<td>verdict → <code>none</code></td>
<td>Educational/technical content, no brand-promotion pattern</td>
<td>"New paper on speech models, breaking it down 🧵"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Single-brand ambassadors</b></td>
<td>verdict → <code>unknown</code> (excluded by EXCLUSIVE patterns)</td>
<td>"Official ambassador for X" — works for ONE brand only, not available</td>
<td>"Official Brand Ambassador for @OneBrand"</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><b>Too little signal</b></td>
<td>verdict → <code>unknown</code></td>
<td>Too few posts or no clear signal — the system <b>never guesses</b></td>
<td>Account with 3 vague tweets</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h2>4. Accounts that never even reach classification (dropped earlier)</h2>
<p>These are filtered out at Step 2, before any bucket logic runs — they are not saved at all.</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Dropped because</th><th>Threshold</th><th>Example</th></tr>
<tr><td>Too few followers</td><td><code>followers &lt; 100</code></td><td>Brand-new / inactive account</td></tr>
<tr><td>No tweets</td><td><code>tweets &lt; 1</code></td><td>Empty/parked handle</td></tr>
<tr><td>No name (suspended?)</td><td><code>name length = 0</code></td><td>Suspended / deleted</td></tr>
<tr><td>Low base score</td><td><code>overall &lt; 10</code></td><td>100 followers, no bio, no website</td></tr>
<tr><td>Recently fetched</td><td>seen in last <b>6 days</b></td><td>Already fresh in the DB — skipped to save quota</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>5. Decision flow — one picture</h2>
<pre>Account discovered
   │
   ├─ &lt;100 followers / no tweets / no name / score &lt; 10 ........ DROPPED (not saved)
   │
   ├─ PR Page / Brand Page ................................... TRACK B (ads only — not in A1/A2)
   │
   └─ Track A (person / creator)
         │
         ├─ openly offers paid work OR #ad / code / affiliate ... 💰 A1 — Confirmed
         │
         ├─ no disclosure, but promotes 2+ brands w/ evidence ... A2 (inferred)
         │       │
         │       ├─ authenticity ≥ 60 ......................... ✦ A2 — Genuine
         │       ├─ authenticity &lt; 60 ......................... ⚠ Salesy / Low
         │       └─ authenticity not scored yet .............. ◷ A2 — Unscored
         │
         ├─ only own product / researcher / journalist ........ none  (Other — not in A1/A2)
         ├─ single-brand "official ambassador" ................ unknown (excluded)
         └─ too few posts / no signal ......................... unknown (Other — not in A1/A2)</pre>

<h2>6. Quick reference — exact conditions</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Bucket</th><th>Condition</th></tr>
<tr><td>💰 A1 — Confirmed</td><td><code>track='A' AND promotion_type='explicit'</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>✦ A2 — Genuine</td><td><code>track='A' AND promotion_type='inferred' AND authenticity_score &gt;= 60</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>⚠ Salesy / Low</td><td><code>track='A' AND promotion_type='inferred' AND authenticity_score &lt; 60</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>◷ A2 — Unscored</td><td><code>track='A' AND promotion_type='inferred' AND authenticity_score IS NULL</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>(not shown) Other / unbadged</td><td><code>track='A' AND promotion_type IN ('none','unknown')</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>(not shown) Track B</td><td><code>track='B'</code></td></tr>
</table>

<hr>
<p style="color:#777;font-size:9pt">
KiteAI X Agent — classification reference. Authenticity threshold = 60 (GENUINE_THRESHOLD).
A2 verdicts require quoted post evidence; the system never guesses (defaults to "unknown").
</p>

</body></html>
